The Herald Tadious Manyepo Sports Reporter WARRIORS midfielderÂ Marvelous Nakamba is scheduled to join Luton Town on loan for the next six months. He is reported to be undergoing medicals at the English Championship football side right now. Aston Villa has since agreed to the loan deal with the English Premiership-chasing side who are currently seventh in the second tier. Nakamba has been out of favour at the Birmingham team with Manager Unai Emery telling him to look for options outside Villa Park. And Nakamba will have an opportunity to revive his career at Luton where he has a chance to get better game time.